Rwanda and Congo May Build New Electricity Plant Using Lake Kivu Methane

-- B y   H e a t h e r   M u r d o c k   a n d   M i c h a e l   J .   K a v a n a g h
-- 
2011-04-27T17:23:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-27/rwanda-and-congo-may-build-new-electricity-plant-using-lake-kivu-methane.html
Rwanda  and the Democratic Republic
of Congo may build a 200 megwatt power plant that will be fueled
by methane gas from Lake Kivu, Colette Ruhamya, Rwanda’s
minister of state for energy and water, said.  “Officials from both countries are currently working to
raise funds for a feasibility study,” she said by phone from
Kigali, Rwanda’s capital.  Congo’s Energy Minister Gilbert Tshiongo Tshibinkubula
declined to comment when contacted today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Heather Murdock in Kigali at 
 hmurdock1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Emily Bowers at 
 ebowers1@bloomberg.net  